import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    chart = sns.countplot(x="zip_code", data=data, order=data['zip_code'].value_counts().index)
    chart.set_xticklabels(chart.get_xticklabels(), rotation=90)
    return chart

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="darkgrid")
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    ax = sns.countplot(x="city", data=data, order=data['city'].value_counts().index)
    ax.set_xticklabels(ax.get_xticklabels(), rotation=90, ha="right")
    ax.set_xlabel("City")
    ax.set_ylabel("Count")
    plt.title("What is the distribution of cities in the dataset?", wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.dropna(subset=['state'])
    state_counts = data['state'].value_counts()
    state_counts_df = pd.DataFrame({'state': state_counts.index, 'count': state_counts.values})
    chart = sns.barplot(x='state', y='count', data=state_counts_df)
    chart.set_xticklabels(chart.get_xticklabels(), rotation=90)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of states in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.dropna(subset=['county'])
    county_counts = data['county'].value_counts().reset_index()
    county_counts.columns = ['county', 'count']
    county_counts = county_counts.sort_values(by='count', ascending=False)
    county_counts = county_counts.head(10)
    county_counts['county'] = county_counts['county'].str.title()
    county_counts = county_counts.merge(data[['county', 'state']].drop_duplicates(), on='county', how='left')
    county_counts['state'] = county_counts['state'].str.upper()
    county_counts['county_state'] = county_counts['county'] + ', ' + county_counts['state']
    county_counts = county_counts[['county_state', 'count']]
    county_counts = county_counts.set_index('county_state')
    county_counts = county_counts.T
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 5))
    sns.heatmap(county_counts, cmap='Blues', annot=True, fmt='g')
    plt.title('Which counties have the highest concentration of data points?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
